  "prompt": "What's the average number of answers to each question on Quora?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, Quora has not publicly released specific statistics regarding the average number of answers per question. The number of answers a question receives on Quora can vary significantly based on several factors, including:\n\n1. **Topic Popularity:** Questions on highly popular or trending topics tend to attract more answers.\n2. **Complexity and Clarity:** Well-formulated and thought-provoking questions are more likely to receive multiple responses.\n3. **Community Engagement:** Active and engaged communities within specific subjects can lead to a higher number of answers.\n4. **Timing:** Questions posted during peak activity times may garner more immediate attention and responses.\n\nWhile some questions might receive only a handful of answers, others\u2014especially those that are widely interesting or controversial\u2014can attract dozens or even hundreds of responses. If you're looking for specific metrics or more detailed insights, you might consider:\n\n- **Exploring Quora's Help Center or Blog:** Sometimes, platforms share user statistics or engagement metrics through official channels.\n- **Contacting Quora Directly:** Reach out to Quora's support or media relations teams for any available data.\n- **Analyzing Public Data:** If you're familiar with data analysis, you could use Quora's public content (to the extent permitted by their terms of service) to calculate an approximate average yourself.\n\nKeep in mind that platform dynamics can change over time, so for the most accurate and up-to-date information, referring directly to Quora or recent studies on the platform would be advisable.",
